<!-- Definition and symptoms -->
'''猩紅熱'''（{{lang-en|Scarlet fever}}）是由A型[[鏈球菌|鏈球菌]]感染造成的疾病。<ref name="CDC2016">{{cite web|url=http://www.cdc.gov/Features/ScarletFever/|title=Scarlet Fever: A Group A Streptococcal Infection|accessdate=12 March 2016|date=January 19, 2016|website=Center for Disease Control and Prevention|archive-date=2016-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312083805/http://www.cdc.gov/Features/ScarletFever/|dead-url=no}}</ref>症狀包括[[喉嚨痛|喉嚨痛]]、[[发热|發燒]]、[[頭痛|頭痛]]、淋巴腫脹以及特殊型態的紅疹。<!-- <ref name=CDC2016/> -->舌頭表面會像砂紙一樣不平整，並呈現紅色。<!-- <ref name=CDC2016/> -->這個疾病通常影響的是5歲到15歲的孩童。<ref name="CDC2016" />

<!-- Cause and diagnosis -->
只有少數有[[链球菌性咽炎|鏈球菌咽炎]]或有鏈球菌皮膚感染的人會發生猩紅熱。<!-- <ref name=CDC2016/> -->此病原菌通常藉由咳嗽或打噴嚏傳播，<!-- <ref name=CDC2016/> -->也可以由人跟人、人跟物之間的接觸傳播。<ref name=CDC2016/>特殊型態的紅疹是由玫紅毒素（erythrogenic toxin）造成，這個物質通常是由某些種類的[[细菌|細菌]]所製造。<ref name=CDC2016/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Ralph|first1=AP|last2=Carapetis|first2=JR|title=Group a streptococcal diseases and their global burden.|journal=Current topics in microbiology and immunology|date=2013|volume=368|pages=1–27|pmid=23242849|doi=10.1007/82_2012_280}}</ref>猩紅熱的診斷靠喉嚨細菌培養。<ref name=CDC2016/>

<!-- Prevention, treatment, and epidemiology -->
目前這個疾病沒有[[疫苗|疫苗]]可以預防。<!-- <ref name=CDC2016/> -->常洗手、不與他人共用個人用品，並且遠離生病的人是比較好的預防方法。<!-- <ref name=CDC2016/> -->這個疾病可以使用[[抗细菌药|抗生素]]治療，避免大多數的併發症。<ref name=CDC2016/>癒後展望通常非常好。<ref name=Quin1989>{{cite journal|last1=Quinn|first1=RW|title=Comprehensive review of morbidity and mortality trends for rheumatic fever, streptococcal disease, and scarlet fever: the decline of rheumatic fever.|journal=Reviews of infectious diseases|date=1989|volume=11|issue=6|pages=928–53|pmid=2690288|doi=10.1093/clinids/11.6.928}}</ref>長期併發症包括腎臟疾病、風濕性心臟病以及關節炎。<ref name=CDC2016/>猩紅熱曾經是二十世紀早期兒童最主要的死因。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Smallman-Raynor|first1=Matthew|title=Atlas of epidemic Britain : a twentieth century picture|date=2012|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|isbn=9780199572922|page=48|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=iMnN4fZrj70C&pg=PA48|access-date=2017-07-08|archive-date=2017-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214073450/https://books.google.ca/books?id=iMnN4fZrj70C&pg=PA48|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Smallman-Raynor|first1=Andrew Cliff, Peter Haggett, Matthew|title=World Atlas of Epidemic Diseases|date=2004|publisher=Hodder Education|location=London|isbn=9781444114195|page=76|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=7WrNBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA76|access-date=2017-07-08|archive-date=2017-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214055650/https://books.google.ca/books?id=7WrNBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA76|dead-url=no}}</ref>

